From 9581294106e9331fbad10a94af6df3f24c3f7ec0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Volker Badziong <development@richtfest.tech>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 10:51:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/8] Support per-server cgroup parent override via
 WINGS_CGROUP_PARENT

Allows a reserved, admin-only egg/server environment variable,
WINGS_CGROUP_PARENT, to override the node-wide docker.cgroup_parent for
a single server. Both the runtime container and the installer container
resolve the override through the same helper, so a server's
installation workloads land under the same slice as its runtime
container.

Panel-supplied values are not trusted: an override must either match an
entry in the new docker.allowed_cgroup_parents allowlist or, when no
allowlist is configured, fall inside the built-in "wings.slice" /
"wings-*.slice" namespace. Values equal to the node-wide default are
always accepted. Anything else fails closed: the override is rejected
with a logged warning that includes the attempted value, and the
node-wide default is used instead.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
